Dialogs.Dialog: All right, I'll work hard again today！
Although I say that, I still need ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s guidance...
Nene
Hehe. work hard, okay？
Yup！
Here I go！
(Hmm, there are a lot of things to remember. Umm, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is...)
Otori
Anegasaki-san！ What was I supposed to do with this？
Ah, that's...
Komari
Nene-san~ Save mee~
Yes, yes. I'm coming right over.
It looks hectic... She has to look after people other than me. It must be tough.
Manager
Nene-kun, about this check...
Even the manager, too！
Good job. So, how is work？
It sounds pathetic, but it's pretty hectic...
Hehe, but you're doing pretty good for someone who just joined, you know？
Is that so...？ By the way, there are a lot of newcomers other than me, I guess.
No, the rest of the staff has all been here for a while. Why？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ has to look after many people, so I thought...
Ah, those girls？
Well, they know what to do and can do the basics on their own, but...
But？
Well, if there's some trouble, or something they don't know, they always come to me...
Even though I'm only a year older than them...
Hey, do you know why they always come to me？
Well, I have no idea...
Hmm... Why is it then...？
(But somehow, I think I know why...)
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Customer
Ah！ Hey！
Ah！ Ah, um... I'm sorry！
Nene
What's wrong...？ Ah！
Our apologies, ma'am. Are your clothes and belongings all right？
Ah, um... Er...
We'll clean it up right away and bring out a new order. We are truly sorry.
Hm, all right...
Sorry...
Eh...？ Oh, don't worry, don't worry.
But... I was the one who did it. ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ shouldn't have to apologize...
That's not right, you know？ From the customer's perspective, we're both staff, right？
But...
Geez... Don't get depressed over this.
Everyone always makes a mistake or two, right？
...Yeah.
Hehe. You're still new, so it's okay if you make lots of mistakes.
But it's no good if you don't learn from them.
It's okay to make mistakes but you have to learn from them, okay？ Everyone here believes in you.
...▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, too？
Of course. You are always obedient, and that is very nice.
Whatever I teach you, you always follow me obediently, right？
That's an amazing thing, you know？
...You think so？
Yup. You can trust this big sister's words, believe me.
Yeah, I believe you. Anyway, I'll try my best so that I don't cause you any more troubles.
Hehe, that's how it should be.
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Nene
Hah！ ...Eh？ What is that？！
In front of the store... There's been an accident！！
Eeeeh！？
What should we do？ The customers are making a commotion, and the manager isn't here...
It's all right. I just called for an ambulance.
Eh？ Ah... With your cell phone？
Yeah. I ran right away into the kitchen... I did it on my own. Was that bad？
No. That was a good decision. It's just what I hoped would happen.
Phew... I think this is it, then.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, what's wrong？
Oh... Thanks for earlier. I wasn't sure what was going to happen.
No problem. Fortunately, it wasn't a serious accident.
Yeah.
But just what I'd expect from a boy. I guess I'm a bit impressed.
I'm a bit old to be called a "boy"...
I see. Hehe, sorry. You're a fine man, aren't you？
If you say it like that...
Well then！
Let's work hard for a bit longer until closing.
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Nene
Thank you very much.
Whew... Good work. The peak is finally over.
There were a lot of customers today... Ah, I'll bus that table.
Really？ Thank you. Hehe...
What is it？
You've memorized most of the jobs. You can even use the cash register.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is to thank for that.
Really？ Then I wonder if my help will no longer be needed. This big sister will be lonely.
That's not the case.
Hehe, Just joking！ It'd be a problem if you didn't quickly become independent.
Independent...？
Ah, I know. How about we celebrate your becoming independent？
Celebrate？
We get off at the same time tonight, right？ If you have some time after, how about getting some food？
...It's going to be just ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ and me？ Just the two of us？
It's fine if you don't want to... Sorry. Did I get ahead of myself？
No, I didn't mean that at all.
Then you will go？
Yeah, of course.
Hehe, I'm glad. Then it's decided.
Welcome！ ...So, see you after work.
Nene
I'm sorry we ended up in such a place...
Don't worry. It's fine.
Hah... To think I would mistake the regular holiday of my favorite place...
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ might have a surprising clumsy side...)
Hm？ I feel a pitying gaze...
T-That's not the case！
Well then, since today is a celebration, this will be my treat.
Eh？ It's fine. You don't need to...
Don't hold back. Whether it's at work or school, you're my junior.
No, that's not good
Sure. But next time I'll treat you
Then I'll take you up on your offer...
Even if you're my senior, we're only a year apart. And we're both students.
...Hmm, if that's what you think.
Don't make fun of me like that...
No, I didn't. It's just what I honestly thought.
Ah, he got to show off.
T-That's not the case...
Hehe. In due time then, okay？
(Seems like it was left unsettled...)
That's right. Obediently listen to this big sister, okay？
Yeah, sorry...
Geez, it's not something you need to apologize for, right？ Hehe, so cute▼
Thanks for today. And sorry. I was the one who invited you and we ended up in this noisy place.
Don't worry. I'd like to thank you.
Hehe. Well, we're celebrating your becoming independent after all.
Ah！ Oh no, the time... I had fun today. Thanks. See you later.
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ and I had a meal together, eh？ It was just fast food, but...)
Okay, I don't have work today. What should I do...？
Go to the arcade, or the bookstore...？ Or go home for some sleep？ What should I do...？
Hm？ Isn't that... ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲？
Nene
Oh, you're welcome.
It's fine, it's fine. I don't need anything... Yeah. Bye-bye, grandma.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Ah...
What were you doing there？
She asked me for directions, so I guided her there.
Hmm, that's what I would expect from ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Expect？
Yeah, whether it's at Dixie's or downtown, you're very dependable.
Hm... Today, a foreigner asked me to help taking a picture. And before that, a lost child grabbed onto the hem of my skirt...
...It's like in a comic book, with all that happening...
I like being relied on and doing things for other people, but...
...I'm not even that reliable of a person...
No way...
It's true.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, do you occasionally want someone to rely on？
Huh？
When you're tired from being relied on so much, wouldn't it be okay for ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ to rely on others too？
Others... Like... You？
I... I might not be of any help. Haha.
Geez, you're pushing yourself...
But, you know. You might be the first person to say that to me...
I'm going this way. See you later...
Okay, see you...
(The true ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, huh...？)
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Phew, finally a break...
Nene
Sorry. Do you have a moment？
Yeah, I was just about to go on break. What is it？
Well... The manager asked me to come up with ideas for a new menu.
Even though you're a part-timer？
Because I'm a part-timer, that is. After all, I'm a high school student, right？
Oh, so a new menu that's popular with high school students？
Right. A menu to attract the younger crowd.
Both boys and girls...？ Might be hard.
So I was thinking... This would be hard to do by myself, right？
Are you saying...
Yup. Could you help me out？ I was thinking I could already rely on you. Hehe.
We can eat at places that are popular with high school students, and decide if there is anything we can put on our menu.
It looks like they'll give us the money for it, too.
Really...？
I'll take care of reporting it, so all you need to do is give your honest opinion.
I just need to give my opinion on the food...？ Why not？
Geez, this is for work, you know？
Yeah, I understand...
Hehe, are you free this Sunday？
Yeah, I'm free.
I'll tell you the details later then. Bye！
(This Sunday... Just the two of us...？)
Hmm... This rice cake isn't very sweet...
Nene
But we can't say that the taste is bland, right？
Yeah. When it got into my mouth, I could feel the flavor melting out... It tastes like Spring.
Phew, I think this should do.
I gave my honest opinion. I wonder if it was okay.
It's okay, it's okay. I'll take care of the rest.
About today...
Hmm？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, you're really good at everything. I've never seen you not being able to do anything.
Is... that so？
You know lots of things, have the ability to act, and can handle everything better than a normal high school student can do.
...Really？
Hey, what kind of person do you see me as？
Someone who is devoted to others
Someone who scolds others strictly
Someone who spoils others
Hmm... I see. So you like someone who's devoted to you？
T-That's not what I said...
Ah... That hurts. I'm supposed to be kind, you know？
You're really strict at work, but sometimes you spoil me...
Saying that... Are you scheming something？
N-No, I'm not.
Thanks for today. You really helped me.
No, I didn't do anything at all.
Hehe, you helped a lot.
Somehow, today was like... a date, huh？
Eh！？
Now I have to go. Bye-bye...
(That surprised me...)
(Still, when she asked me the question earlier, she had such a sad face. I wonder what that was...)
Nene
Wow... It's so crowded.
Anyway, I wouldn't have imagined that we would investigate a noodles house...
Well, their chilled noodles are very delicious.
It's really delicious... So, this is what one can expect from a famous noodles shop, I guess...
Hehe. It must be hard for our restaurant to imitate the taste, right？
And to think about the cooking equipment...
Eh？ What is it？
It's just so obvious that you are really older than me.
Huh, is that so？
Yes, you know a lot and you can do so many things. The way you investigated that shop was way beyond a highschooler's ability.
...Really？
Hey, what kind of person do you see me as？
Someone who is devoted to others
Someone who scolds others strictly
Someone who spoils others
I see... So you like someone to be devoted to you？
T-That's not how I meant it...
Eh？ I thought I've been very kind to you all this time.
But you are strict when it comes to work and you scolded me a lot.
Hehe, you want to be spoiled？
It's not about me！
Thanks for today. Because of you, I could get the report done.
I didn't...
Hehe, you really worked hard, you know？
Somehow, today was like a date, wasn't it？
Eh！？
Ah, I have to go... See you later.
(That surprised me...)
(Still, when she asked me that question earlier, she had such a sad face. I wonder what that was...)
Nene
This place is famous for making pasta with seasonal ingredients. Now it's Fall, so mushrooms would taste great.
...Say. Do you think you and I are a bit out of place here？
That's not the case, you know. Surprisingly, students at our school come here quite often.
I see...
If I say I don't know how to describe this dish... it's probably useless as a reference...
Hm, somehow, it's also about the atmosphere...
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is definitely an adult.
What are you saying all of the sudden？
When we're together, I might look a bit like a child...
That's...
You know lots of things, have the ability to act, and handle everything better than a normal high school student can do.
As I thought...
From your perspective, what kind of person do you see me as？
Someone who is devoted to others
Someone who scolds others strictly
Someone who spoils others
Hmm, so you have such a desire...
T-That's not how I meant it...
How cruel. I'm supposed to be kind, you know？
But you know right from wrong. At work, you're precise, strict, and competent.
Geez, have I been spoiling you...？ Hehe▼
That's not what I meant...
Thanks. With your help, I think I'll be able to write a good report.
I didn't do anything...
Hehe, you were some help, you know？
Somehow, do you think today was kind of like a date？
Eh！？
See you later. Bye-bye...
(That surprised me...)
(Still, when she asked me that question earlier, she had such a sad face. I wonder what that was...)
Wow, so there was a place like this...
Nene
There's a good atmosphere, right？ It's right on the lake's shore. And you can only get this lasagna during the Winter.
Eating warm food while gazing at the winter lake... Hehe, how wonderful.
Yeah, the food is delicious. I sure want to come here again...
If we could reproduce this taste in a family restaurant, it'd be amazing.
If we want to reproduce the taste, then...
I just thought about it again today...
What is it？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is an adult, definitely.
You know everything; you have the ability to act; your work ethic would put most members of society to shame...
That's not the case...
What kind of person do you see me as？
Someone who is devoted to others
Someone who scolds others strictly
Someone who spoils others
Hmm, so you have such a desire.
T-That's not how I meant it...
How cruel. I'm supposed to be kind, you know？
But you know right from wrong. At work, you are precise, strict, and competent.
Geez, have I been spoiling you...？ Hehe.
That's not what I meant...
Thanks. With your help, I think I'll be able to write a good report.
I didn't do anything...
Hehe, you were some help, you know？
So I wonder... Was this a date？
Eh！？
See you later. Bye-bye...
(That surprised me...)
(Still, when she asked me that question earlier, she had such a sad face. I wonder what that was...)
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Phew, done with the trash.
Nene
Ah, taking out the trash？
Yeah, how about you？
I'm on break, so I thought I'd get some fresh air... Say, do you have a minute？
Yeah, I'm also going on break now. Want to go to the break room？
No, here...
...？ Well, okay...
Sorry for asking you a strange question last time...
Last time...？
When we were out investigating for the new menu at the manager's request.
Ah...
"What kind of person do you see me as？" As if. It's a bothersome question, isn't it？
You can just forget about it.
I was more concerned about ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s sad face as you asked that...
Eh...
If you have anything worrying you...
Geez！ Don't get ahead of yourself！
I was just teasing you.
What！？
After all, you make the cutest faces when you're troubled.
No way...
Yes, that face. Hehe, so cute▼
Ah, I have to get back...
Hm？
I don't know if I'm reliable or helpful at all.
If being one-sidedly treated as mature is tough...
...Geez, saying that with such a cute face...
Thanks. See you later.
(The sad ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ and her attitude just now...)
(Which one is her true self...？)
I came to the station because I was bored, but there isn't anything interesting here...
Ah, that's right. The manager gave me a ticket to a movie premiere...
(Hmm, that was pretty interesting.)
Nene
Eh？
Ah... ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
What a coincidence. I thought I recognized this person from somewhere.
Er... Is ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ here for the premiere too？
Yeah, I watched it too. The manager gave me a ticket... Wait, did he？
Yeah, I got mine from the manager too.
Hehe. Well, I guess it wasn't a coincidence then.
Guess so. What did you think of the movie？
Oh, it was interesting.
I see. But this is a horror movie...
...Is it strange for a girl to like horror...？
It's not strange...
Is that so？ Then good. I was thinking of seeing it again.
You liked it that much？ Well, it was interesting. It might be worth watching again...
Ah, hey. In that case, how about we go see it together？
Together？
Ah, do you not want to？
No, that's not the case.
Then how about it？ Seeing the movie together...
Yeah, let's do that.
...Hehe.
Hm？
This time it's not on the way home after work or for an errand, right？
Ah...
Ah, sorry. I have to get going. ...See you later.
(This time, it might really be a date...)
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Thank you very much.
Otori
Hey, so you're already a veteran, aren't you？
Eh？ That's not the case...
Komari
That is the case. Help me if there's something I don't know, okay？
Geez, you rely on people too much.
But Nene-san hasn't paid attention to me lately.
Eh？
Nene
Good work.
Ah, good work.
You have a break after this, right？ Can I have a moment？
Ah, yeah...
See, see. It's definitely true.
No way. Really？
Say, what are you doing on your next day off？
Huh？
You remember？ That movie premiere from before. It's in theater now, you know？
Ah, is it？ Then we have to go.
...We "have to go"？
Yeah. After all, we promised to, right？
Ah... Yeah. That's right...
What？ Something's wrong？
No... That's right. We promised, so we have to go.
Then how about next Sunday？ It's ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s day off too, right？
Yeah, right. Let's go with that.
Okay. Well, then let's get back to work.
Yeah, let's.
Er, row D... Our seats are D15 and D16... Okay！ ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, over here.
Nene
Ah... Right in the middle.
We already know the plot, but the visuals were good too. We can enjoy it again.
Yeah, that's right...
...Are you a bit down？
No, I'm not...
Really？
Say...
...Hmm？
Do you often talk with them？
...Them？
...The two from Dixie's.
Ah. Yeah, I do. Relatively often, I guess.
We go to different schools, but we're the same grade. We talk about our classes and stuff.
I see. The same grade...
What's wrong？
Hey, what do you think of those two？
Eh！？
Hmm, let's see...
I think they're cute
I think they're a bit troublesome
I think they're childish
They're cute. They're like classmates and are easy to talk to.
...I see. So you like cute girls...
Ah, it's not about if I like them or not... Should I say I feel like I want to protect them...？
They're good girls, but they can be a bit troublesome. They like to rely on others...
I see. So you prefer people who work hard on their own？
I guess so. I think people who can handle their surroundings are pretty cool.
They're good girls, but for being the same age, they seem a bit childish.
Hmm, so you like girls who are more mature？
I wonder... I might hope for a girl who is nice and forgives me for everything...
Ah, it's starting.
Yeah...
As I thought, that was really good！
Yeah, and even though I knew what would happen, I still got pretty scared.
Hehe, I'm glad I invited you.
I'm glad to have been invited.
I feel stupid for worrying about it...
No, it's nothing.
Hey, for today's ...date, did you enjoy it？
Hmm？ Yeah, of course.
I see. That's good then... Bye.
(That's the usual ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, right？)
Komari
Eh？ No way！ And then？
So then, the teacher's face was like...
Nene
Hey, isn't your break almost over？
Otori
Ah, yes...
Nene-san is scary！
Well then, I have to get going too.
All right, I'll work hard again today！
(It's pretty busy today...)
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲！ Are you okay？
Ah, yeah. Sorry.
Ah... Be careful. Newly washed plates are usually slippery.
Yeah, you're right...
What's wrong？
Nothing. I'm just thinking that you might be the more reliable one now.
That's because of ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s good leadership.
Geez, you're saying something cheeky...
Anyway, we need to clean this up...
Ah, I'll take care of it. It's fine.
It's rare for Nene-san to break a plate. Are you all right？
That's right. Did you get injured？
No, I'm fine...
You look pale. Don't overwork yourself...
...That's right. I think I'll rest for a bit. I'll be right back...
All right, I'll work hard again today！
Nene
Welcome.
Please wait a moment.
Thank you very much.
Yup, it's the usual ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Phew, I'm tired...
Good work.
You know. Today I felt an extremely hot gaze.
That's...
Did I make you worry？
...Yeah.
Ah, I'm a failure as a big sister to let you worry about me...
Sorry...
Geez, it's not something you should apologize for.
But...
I decided to stop worrying about them...
...About what？
Various things.
You know, I had a lot of things to worry about.
But you see, I've decided to stop worrying.
Why？
Because I realized it was useless to worry about them.
After all, I'm me, and you're you, right？
Y-Yeah...
Bye...
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, and I'm me？ Is it a personal philosophy of some sort？)
(I'm confused...)
Nene
Ah, good work.
Say...
...Yeah？
About what you said earlier...
...Earlier？
That you were worrying about something...
Ah, that. You care about that？
That's... Of course.
Well, it was about... the date with you.
I was really looking forward to it. But then you said "We have to go" and "Because we promised."
As if it was an obligation, and that it couldn't be helped...
Sorry, I didn't mean it like that...
Yeah, I understand that... But, well... Um...
When you were having fun with those girls, the girls who are in the same grade as you...
Well... They're work colleagues...
That's right. That sort of thing is quite obvious...
But you know, this is me.
With just one of your casual words, my heart greatly wavers.
When I saw you having fun with someone of the same age, I became jealous.
But you know, I decided to accept that part of myself.
After all, this is who I am...
Nene
Nice work.
Um...
...Huh？
About what you said earlier...
...Earlier？
That you were worrying about something...
Ah, that. You care about that？
That's... Of course.
That was about the date... with you.
I was really looking forward to it.
But then you said "We have to go" and "Because we promised"...
Geez. It sounded as if it was an obligation that you had to go with me.
Sorry, I didn't mean it like that...
Hehe, but it's okay now.
When you were having fun with those girls, I didn't like it.
Well... They're work colleagues...
That's right. I should've realized that...
But, this is what I am.
I'd feel bad if someone else had taken you away from me.
That's why I've decided.
Nene
Nice work.
Um...
...What？
About what you said earlier...
What did I say？
That you were worrying about something...
Hehe, about that？ You care about it？
Well... of course.
It was about the date... with you.
Because I was really looking forward to it.
And then you said "We have to go" and "Because we promised"...
If you wanted to go with me, you would've said "Let's go" but you didn't.
Sorry, I didn't mean it like that...
Hehe. But it's fine now.
I saw you enjoying your time with those girls who are in the same grade as you...
Well... They're work colleagues...
Yeah, that's quite natural then.
But, now I don't care about that anymore.
Whatever you say, or whatever you do, I won't be caring too much about it anymore.
That's my resolution.
